race.comment: The staying race of the day, for the maidens, a number of whom have demonstrated a hankering for getting out to this trip. ZINOVATION (7) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1755m at Geelong, beaten 3 lengths, but will have come on from that and needs this sort of trip to be a winning hope. SUNGAZER (10) missed the frame first-up but has improved in subsequent runs, finishing in the money last start over 2000m at Murray Bridge. DOUBTA (8) should be peaking now and could race handier up in trip from the gun draw. I BELONG (14) hasn't done much in her two career runs but gets a chance to feature here.
